It’s #throwbackthursday 🙌 and today we’re celebrating @laurakraut and Cedric on their historical victory winning the $500,000 Grand Prix CSI5*! 💪

Her and her mount raced against the clock followed by the eyes of 7,000 SPECTATORS 👀 to watch her during the 2011 FTI Winter Equestrian Festival. 🌟 The crowd went wild for this fantastic performance, creating a beautiful atmosphere in the sport. 

Laura Kraut and the 1998 Holsteiner gelding of Happy Hill Farm secured their winning time of 35.86 seconds in the jump-off. 👏

What a moment to remember!! 🥰

#TransformationTuesday: From riding lessons at the age of three to three time Olympian,  Laura Kraut’s journey is a testament to hard work and dedication ✨ Encouraged by her mother, Laura’s early riding lessons paved the way for an extraordinary career that’s taken her to the top of the sport 🏆

Kraut’s sporting philosophy has proven that hard work conquers all: “As in anything, be prepared for a lot of long hours, a lot of hard work, a lot of frustration and a lot of reward” ✨

Laura’s accomplishments over the years read like an odyssey – from being named the 2021 International Equestrian of the Year 🎖️by the USEF to receiving the prestigious USOC Jack Kelly Fair Play Award in 2003 🏅. Her talent and dedication shone through as she was named the AGA Rider of the Year for the 2000/01 season 🏆

In 2018, Kraut was part of the Gold 🥇medal winning team at the Beijing Olympics 🇨🇳 , riding Cedric. Fast forward to 2020, Kraut made history at the Tokyo Olympics 🇯🇵, becoming the oldest US female athlete to win an Olympic medal since 1904, securing a silver🥈 in team equestrian jumping at the age of 55. 

Her remarkable legacy includes a team silver 🥈at the 2006 FEI World Equestrian Games, a gold🥇 in 2018, and a bronze 🥉team medal in 2016 at the FEI Jumping Nations Cup™ Finals, followed by a silver 🥈in 2017. Notably, she was a part of the first all-women 🎀 team at the FEI Jumping Nations Cup CSIO5* Dublin in 2017 🇮🇪 This year, she played a pivotal role in Team USA’s 🇺🇸 victories🏆🏆, both at the FEI Jumping Nations Cup of the USA in San Juan Capistrano 🇺🇸 with Dorado 212 and the FEI Jumping Nations Cup of Mexico 🇲🇽 with Baloutinue.

Currently ranked 22nd in the world 🌎 , recent victories with her remarkable horses, including Baloutinue, Calgary Tame, Bisquetta, and Confu, have continued to solidify Laura’s place at the top of the sport 🔝🏆

Laura Kraut has become a true legend and icon in the world of showjumping ❤️With so many accomplishments in her career so far, we can’t wait to see what else the future holds for the exceptional rider! 🌟
